article.description: Star Allen scored 21 points and Jantel Lavender added 17, and each had two baskets in a 15-3 surge to end the half, to lead Ohio State (No. 14 ESPN/USA Today, No. 15 AP) to a 59-51 win over Indiana on Sunday.
article.headline: No. 14 Ohio State edges Indiana to hold on to first place in Big Ten
article.linkText: No. 14 Ohio State rallies late to get past Indiana
article.story:
COLUMBUS, Ohio -- Star Allen scored 21 points and Jantel Lavender added 17, and each had two baskets in a 15-3 surge to end the half, to lead Ohio State (No. 14 ESPN/USA Today, No. 15 AP) to a 59-51 win over Indiana on Sunday.

The victory kept the Buckeyes (18-3, 9-1 Big Ten), chasing a fifth consecutive Big Ten title, in first place in the conference.

Indiana (15-5, 8-3) led throughout the first half and was on top by nine points before the Buckeyes took the lead for good. Lavender had five points and Allen four in the 15-3 run.

Ohio State, up 32-29 at the half, then slowly added to its lead.

Allen also had 13 rebounds and Lavender nine.

Jori Davis had 15 points, Whitney Thomas 12 and Jamie Braun 10 for the Hoosiers, who had briefly led the Big Ten until a stunning 61-52 upset at Illinois a week earlier.
